Wash and dry produce.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #pot. Cook @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz}, breaking
up meat into pieces, until mostly cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

In a #bowl, mix @cornstarch{1%tbsp} with 1 TBSP water until smooth and no lumps remain.
> TIP: Mix with your finger to ensure there are no lumps!

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2}, cornstarch mixture, half the
@Italian herb paste{1%tbsp}, and 2 cups water into pot with sausage.

Cover pot and bring to a boil. Stir in @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @tortelloni{9%oz}, and
@spinach{5%oz}. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened,
tortelloni are tender, and sausage is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt if desired.

While soup cooks, trim @scallions{2}; chop greens (save whites for
another use). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Cut @demi-baguette{1} in half lengthwise; toast until golden brown. Spread
with half the @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp}; halve on a diagonal.

Top soup with @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, scallion greens, and a squeeze of lemon.
Serve with garlic bread.

> Chicken Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.